Notes: Muskleg Lake pack (7 wolves) was the only pack with pack specific data but only their moose kills were reported and no moose/wolf or moose kg/wolf was reported for that year or moose abundance was reported in an extractable way. Funny enough, they were the only point in which the 5.5 kg moose/wolf/day and 0.12kg moose/kg wolf/day was reported. So couldn't do pack specific extraction because it would only be a single data point. Wolves were assumed to be an average of 46kg based on 5 wolves (2 adults 3 pups) poisoned and measured in the study area in 1980
elk adults made up 35% of elk kills and 65% of the elk pop
